To produce a new openjpeg release:

1. Generate the CHANGES for the release:

$ ./genchange.sh

copy the branch

$ svn copy https://openjpeg.googlecode.com/svn/branches/openjpeg-1.5 https://openjpeg.googlecode.com/svn/tags/version.1.5
$ svn add CHANGES https://openjpeg.googlecode.com/svn/tags/version.1.5

2. Generates the source tarball + binary tarball:

$ ./release.sh

If you have a windows box, from a CMD console:

> release.bat

You can use googlecode_upload.py to upload your files directly:

$ googlecode-upload.py -s "Version 1.5 source files of OpenJPEG library and codecs" -p openjpeg /tmp/openjpeg_release/openjpeg-build/openjpeg-1.5.0.tar.gz
$ googlecode-upload.py -s "Version 1.5 Linux Binaries of OpenJPEG library and codecs" -p openjpeg /tmp/openjpeg_release/openjpeg-build/OPENJPEG-1.5.0-Linux.tar.gz

